  "body": "This is specified here: https://github.com/ethereum/devp2p/blob/master/rlpx.md#version-5-eip-706-september-2017\r\n\r\nOur enterprise-only TLS P2P implementation (a modified version of the RLPx spec) does not include encryption, a MAC or compression. Encryption/MAC are replaced with TLS, however compression remains unimplemented. It is still a desirable feature to reduce unnecessary data traffic as explained in https://eips.ethereum.org/EIPS/eip-706\r\n\r\nThe TLS P2P implementation uses TLS v1.3 which has removed compression due to security flaws, so compression via TLS is not an option.\r\n\r\nThe recommendation is to use Snappy Compression similar to the original RLPx implementation, preferably reusing the same code for both TLS and non-TLS modes.",
